channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Former NBC/CNN Reporter Calls Dinner Guests 'MAGAts' When They Don't Share Her TDS
NY v. Trump trial resumes with 'star witness' Michael Cohen expected to take the stand
item.description: Former Trump attorney Michael Cohen is expected to take the stand Monday morning to testify in the criminal trial of former President Trump.

item.title: Michael Cohen to Testify Against Trump for Payment He Made for Him
item.description: Donald Trump's estranged former fixer Michael Cohen is expected to begin giving testimony Monday that could determine whether jurors convict the former U.S. president for calling a payment to a lawyer a legal expense.

item.title: Politics Downstream From Culture: Was Andrew Breitbart Wrong?
Republican says Biden has 'strengthened' Hamas by withholding aid from Israel: 'Completely incompetent'
item.description: Sen. Pete Ricketts, R-NE, said President Biden was 'absolutely mismanaging' Israel's war with Hamas after he threatened to withhold high payload bombs from America's ally.

item.title: W.Va. Senate GOP Primary Winner Likely to Succeed Manchin
item.description: After Sen. Joe Manchin, D-W.Va., decided not to run for reelection, it is expected that a Republican will be the successor to that Senate seat.

item.title: All in the family: 5 Trump kin to represent Florida at Republican National Convention
item.description: Barron, Tiffany, Donald Junior and Eric Trump, along with Kimberly Guilfoyle and Michael Boulos were Trump family members selected to the Florida RNC delegation.

item.title: Biden Looks to Clooney, Obama, Clintons for Fundraising
item.description: President Joe Biden's campaign is set to host a major fundraiser in Los Angeles next month and will seek the help of former Presidents Barack Obama and Bill Clinton, as well as movie stars George Clooney and Julia Roberts, to attract more support for his campaign.

item.title: Howard University Cancels Graduation MID-CEREMONY in Chaotic Scene
Conservative Senate firebrand is number one target of Dems: 'They're coming after me'
item.description: Republican Ted Cruz of Texas, a conservative firebrand in the Senate, is highlighting his bipartisan chops as he runs for re-election.

item.title: Longtime Clinton Adviser: Biden Must Change Strategy to Win
item.description: Focusing on the left wing of the Democratic Party instead of independent voters could cost President Joe Biden the election this November, according to a New York Times opinion piece on Sunday written by Mark Penn.

item.title: Biden Makes Truly Strange, Snippy Comment Coming Out of Church in Delaware for Mother's Day
Hillary Clinton slammed by fellow Democrat for 'dismissive' remarks about anti-Israel protesters
item.description: Sen. Chris Van Hollen, D-Md., said Hillary Clinton was "quite dismissive" when she said anti-Israel protesters "don't know very much...about the history of the Middle East."

item.title: Jake Sullivan: Biden Will Ensure Israel Has What It Needs to Defend Itself
item.description: Despite President Joe Biden's threat to withhold offensive weapons from Israel, he will make sure the Jewish state has what it needs to defend itself, White House national security adviser Jake Sullivan told ABC News' "This Week with George Stephanopoulos" on Sunday."
